=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: 4-hydroxybenzaldehyde + 2-chloro-4,6-dimethoxypyrimidine, K2CO3 (or Cs2CO3), DMF, heat → 4-(4,6-dimethoxypyrimidin-2-yloxy)benzaldehyde, O=Cc1ccc(Oc2nc(OC)cc(OC)n2)cc1 | Step 2: Horner-Wadsworth-Emmons olefination of this aldehyde with triethyl phosphonoacetate/NaH (or DBU) → EtO2C/C=C/c1ccc(Oc2nc(OC)cc(OC)n2)cc1 | Step 3: Reduce the ester with DIBAL-H to the allylic alcohol HOCH2/C=C/c1ccc(Oc2nc(OC)cc(OC)n2)cc1 | Step 4: Convert the alcohol to the allylic bromide BrCH2/C=C/c1ccc(Oc2nc(OC)cc(OC)n2)cc1 using PBr3 or Appel conditions | Step 5: In parallel, acylate glycine methyl ester with 2,6-dichlorobenzoyl chloride (Et3N or Na2CO3) to give methyl N-(2,6-dichlorobenzoyl)glycinate, COC(=O)CH2NC(=O)c1c(Cl)cccc1Cl | Step 6: Deprotonate this glycine derivative at the α-position with LDA or NaHMDS and alkylate with the allylic bromide from Step 4 to install the intact homoallylic aryl side chain, giving the exact target COC(=O)C(C/C=C/c1ccc(Oc2nc(OC)cc(OC)n2)cc1)NC(=O)c1c(Cl)cccc1Cl.

